\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 A {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SharedUniverse"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Shared Universe}} which spawned its own genre, known as \'93{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NonFiction"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Non-Fiction}}\'94. Despite the various problems noted at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealityIsUnrealistic"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Reality Is Unrealistic}}, it is almost universally agreed that there is no other universe known so thoroughly worked out from established scientific principles. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/NASA"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 The Apollo Program}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/WorldWarII"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 World War II}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 and}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Woodstock"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Woodstock}} fall in this class.\

